A true viſible Church of Jeſus Chriſt is not a profane, wicked aſſembly, an aſſembly of Notorious Drunkards, Whoremongers Swearers, and the like; But an holy aſſembly, called out from among theſe;
1 Cor. 6.11 
                  Such were ſome of you, but ye are waſhed, but ye are Sanctified.

Thoſe perſons, the Apoſtles received into the Church, as members of it, were not prophane and lewd perſons, ſcandalous, of evill report, ſcoffers at Sanctification, deſpiſers of Gods Ordinances and holy duties;

                     Acts 2 47.4
                        •
                     .49. But they were ſuch as gladly received the Word, as were pricked in their hearts at the ſenſe of their ſins, ſuch as continued in prayer and the exerciſe of other holy and Chriſtian duties: They were ſuch as burnt their curious (becauſe prophane) Books;

                     Acts 19.18, 19. Such as confeſſed their ſins, and ſhewed their deeds.
